               <p>JAMES COLE. I am <rs id="t18340515-138-viclabel758" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340515-138-victim1267 t18340515-138-viclabel758"></join> to Mr. Cox, he keeps the <placeName id="t18340515-138-crimeloc759">Star and Garter, Pall Mall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340515-138-crimeloc759" type="placeName" value="Star and Garter, Pall Mall"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340515-138-crimeloc759" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340515-138-off756 t18340515-138-crimeloc759"></join>. On the 10th of May, the prisoner slept in the same room with me - I missed a shirt and a rasor - this is my shirt.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. STAMMERS. Q. How do you know it is yours? A. By the bosom, which is composed of five different pieces - it was made for me - I never saw one made like it - I had some more made at the same time, but there was not linen enough to make the bosom of this, and it was joined - there is no other mark on it - two other persons slept in the room.</p>
               <p>
            
